snippet.textDisplay:
The time I successfully out ran the police (and why I don’t recommend it):




Many years ago, I was a driver for a transportation company. Drove a V8 crown Vic with a roller cam in it. Man, that car was FAST. Driving Schedule manifest was always very tightly scheduled. Impossible schedule to keep if you always do the speed limit. However if you got three speeding tickets within one year, you were terminated. One day with said tight schedule, I was speeding on my way to the next client. I came through a yellow light over a hill, and there he was. A motorcycle cop. Not on his bike, but parked and standing with a pointing radar gun right at me. He motions for me to pull over. I’m already sitting on two tickets. One more and I would lose my job. As a single mom with a mortgage and food to put on the table, I absolutely could not lose my job. There were cars behind me, none in front, and there was The ability to turn right coming up. I quickly made the decision that I wasn’t stopping. I would take the turn and by the time he got on his motorcycle and made it into traffic, I’d be gone. Also, if he did catch up to me and flip his lights on, I’d just pretend like I hadn’t seen him motion anything. Plus there was a wooded housing development that had been there a long time with mature, thick trees, right down from that turn and I knew it well. So I caught the right, checked the rear and he was nowhere near the turn yet and probably wasn’t even fully in his motorcycle yet, so I turned into that development. Drove to a house in the back and pulled into the driveway that was completely secluded and hidden from street view by trees. And then I sat there for like 15 minutes. Needless to say He never caught me and I never heard any sirens. There was a sweet little old lady that came out of the house and asked why I was in her driveway. I pretended I was looking for a client that I was picking up and that I thought it was her address 🤣 she was so sweet. So yeah. I outran and out smarted the police once. The reason I don’t recommend it? It was a big risk. To big. If he had caught me, I could have been arrested and ticketed with big fines and I would have lost my job anyway. Most of the time, people do not successfully out run the cops. The odds are not in your favor. The wise thing to do would have actually been to talk to him reasonably and explain the issue at my job and plead with him to just give me a warning. Most cops are reasonable and if you’re honest a forthright, they will work with you. They don’t want citizens to lose their jobs. After all, most of them are working parents too. Not only that, but I got yelled out by my boss cause running from the cops made me 20 minutes late to pick up the next client🤣so, when it’s all said and done, would I do it again?? Yeah probably 😂
